title: Grateful Dead Live at Folsom Field, U. of Colorado on 1980-06-07
description: Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil-> El Paso-> Mama Tried, Ramble On Rose, Passenger, Far From Me, Minglewood Blues, Loser, Feel Like A Stranger, Deal Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Althea, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E:Alabama Getaway-> E: One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Bl

Get it just for the Ramble On Rose. I saw another source from this show on dimeadozen.org but was unable to get it. This one will do just fine.

Not a 5 star sound. great show. but honestly it sounds like a bootleg i would have tossed onto the floor of my 1st tour car.

Much finer and cleaner sounding shows to be had .
enjoy the ride.

good show

prescient Weir comment An ok show. It was billed as the "15th anniversary" show. On a Boulder radio station after the show, Weir was asked about this and said "it means nothing to me -- we've played for 15 years, we'll play another 15 years." Prescient.

And Althea for the Ages Great Althea, certainly among my favorite recordings of that song. I can jive with the bootleg feel, though I understand the issues with quality. In the scheme of things, though, I can take the quality with a grain of salt, given that Jerry's guitar riff after the first verse is THE most blistering and awesome I have heard of any althea. Sure, there are some better recordings, but that riff is worth the bootleg sound. (rating would be about 2.5/5 were it not for that awe-inspiring guitar lick.)
